\u1ec7t s\u1eed k\u00fd to\u00e0n th\u01b0}}\n* {{citation|author=Ph\u1ea1m V\u0103n S\u01a1n|title=Vi\u1ec7t s\u1eed to\u00e0n th\u01b0|year=1983|language=Vietnamese|publisher=Association of Vietnameses in Japan|location=Japan|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|first=Martin |last=Stuart-Fox|title=China and Southeast Asia: Tribute, Trade and Influence|publisher=Allen & Unwin|year=2003|isbn=1-86448-954-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|first=Nicholas |last=Tarling|authorlink=Nicholas Tarling|title=The Cambridge History of Southeast Asia|volume=Volume one: From Early Times to C. 1800|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1992|isbn=0-521-35505-2|ref=harv}}\n* Taylor, K. W. (2013). [https://books.google.com/books?id=P2HP31kOSA4C&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''A History of the Vietnamese''] (illustrated ed.). Cambridge University Press. {{ISBN|0521875862}}. Retrieved 7 August 2013.\n* {{citation|first=Keith Weller |last=Taylor|title=The Birth of Vietnam|publisher=University of California Press|year=1991|isbn=0-520-07417-3|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|author=Tham Seong Chee|title=Essays on Literature and Society in Southeast Asia: Political and Sociological Perspectives|year=1981|publisher=NUS Press|location=Singapore|isbn=9971-69-036-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|author=Tr\u1ea7n Tr\u1ecdng Kim|authorlink=Tr\u1ea7n Tr\u1ecdng Kim|title=Vi\u1ec7t Nam s\u1eed l\u01b0\u1ee3c |year=1971|language=Vietnamese|publisher=Center for School Materials|location=Saigon|ref=harv|title-link=Vi\u1ec7t Nam s\u1eed l\u01b0\u1ee3c}}\n* {{citation|author1=Tuyet Nhung Tran |author2=Anthony J. S. Reid |title=Vi\u1ec7t Nam Borderless Histories|year=2006|publisher=University of Wisconsin Press|location=Madison, Wisconsin|isbn=978-0-299-21770-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|author1=Tr\u01b0\u01a1ng H\u1eefu Qu\u00fdnh |author2=\u0110inh Xu\u00e2n L\u00e2m |author3=L\u00ea M\u1eadu H\u00e3n |title=\u0110\u1ea1i c\u01b0\u01a1ng l\u1ecbch s\u1eed Vi\u1ec7t Nam|year=2008|language=Vietnamese|publisher=Education Publishing House|location=Hanoi|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|first=O. W. |last=Wolters|authorlink=O. W. Wolters|publisher= Cornell University Library|title=Monologue, Dialogue, and Tran Vietnam|year=2009|ref=harv|hdl=1813/13117}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Tr\u1ea7n dynasty}}\n* https://ecommons.cornell.edu/bitstream/handle/1813/13117/Wolters_TranVietnam.pdf?sequence=1\n\n{{-}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[L\u00fd dynasty]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Vietnamese dynasties|Dynasty of Vietnam]]|years=1225\u20131400}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[H\u1ed3 dynasty]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{coord|21|01|N|105|51|E|type:country|display=title}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tran Dynasty}}\n[[Category:1400 disestablishments in Asia]]\n[[Category:Former monarchies of Asia]]\n[[Category:Tr\u1ea7n dynasty| ]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1225]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese dynasties]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Vietnamese dynasty}}\n{{for|the dynasty of China|Chen dynasty}}\n{{Infobox country\n|native_name =  {{lang|vi|\u0110\u1ea1i Vi\u1ec7t Qu\u1ed1c}} ({{lang|vi|\u5927\u8d8a\u570b}})\n|conventional_long_name = Kingdom of \u0110\u1ea1i Vi\u1ec7t\n|common_name            = Tr\u1ea7n dynasty\n|status                = '''Kingdom'''\n|era                  = Postclassical Era\n|government_type          = Monarchy\n|\n|year_start          = 1225\n|year_end             = 1400\n|\n|event_start =Coronation of [[Tr\u1ea7n C\u1ea3nh]]\n|date_start  = 10/1/\n|event_end   = [[Tr\u1ea7n Thi\u1ebfu \u0110\u1ebf]] ceded the throne to [[H\u1ed3 Qu\u00fd Ly]]\n|date_end    = 22/3/\n|\n|event1      = Regent of [[Tr\u1ea7n Th\u1eeba]] and [[Tr\u1ea7n Th\u1ee7 \u0110\u1ed9]]\n|date_event1 = 1226\n|event2      = [[Mongol invasions of Vietnam]]\n|date_event2 = 1258,1285 and 1287\u201388\n|event3      = Coup overthrown of [[D\u01b0\u01a1ng Nh\u1eadt L\u1ec5]]\n|date_event3 = 1370\n|\n|event_pre   = \n|date_pre    = \n|\n|<!--- Flag navigation: